cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for optimizing neural networks. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments were conducted on image classification tasks using LeNet and VGG-16 architectures. Additionally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with pruning neurons in neural networks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. Finally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as neural networks are also used in natural language processing tasks.
